title: Dividend per share of Daimler AG 2006 to 2019
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Dividend per share in euros. In total the number of data points it has is 14.
Overall Dividend per share in euros has decreased over the Year.
Dividend per share in euros is roughly constant from 2006 to 2009, gradually increasing from 2009 to 2010, and finally roughly constant from 2010 to 2019.
The line rapidly remained stable by 100.0% from Year 2008 to 2009,increased by 18499999999900.0% from Year 2009 to 2010, and lastly, remained stable by 72.31% from Year 2018 to 2019.
The highest Dividend per share in euros, of value 3.65 was reached at Year 2017
The lowest Dividend per share in euros, of value 0.0 was reported at Year 2009
